HEADWORD: Lovage
<hw>Lov"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>liv⟦egrave⟧che</ets>, fr. L. <ets>levisticum</ets>,
<ets>ligusticum</ets>, a plant indigenous to Liguria, lovage, from
<ets>Ligusticus</ets> Ligustine, Ligurian, <ets>Liguria</ets> a country
of Cisalpine Gaul.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An umbelliferous plant
(<spn>Levisticum officinale</spn>), sometimes used in medicine as an
aromatic stimulant.</def>⟦br⟧
